title: Molina's 3 TDs power SVC in 66-20 victory over Fairmont Prep
text:
Molina's 3 TDs power SVC in 66-20 victory over Fairmont Prep October 25, 2015 3:27 PM By BRIAN REED-BAIOTTO CONTRIBUTING WRITER 
YORBA LINDA - David Molina's three early touchdowns got the Saddleback Valley Christian motor running in the Warriors' 66-20 victory over Fairmont Prep on Saturday evening at Yorba Linda High. 
Molina caught TD passes of 32 and 28 yards from quarterback Cade Henjum , he scored on a 23-yard run and recovered a fumble on defense. 
Henjum threw TD passes of 28, 32, 22 and 25 yards and Dalton Lohman scored twice for Saddleback Valley Christian (8-0). 
Kiki Mendoza scored all three TD's for Fairmont Prep (3-6) on runs of 18 and a pair of 1-yard scores. 
Savai'i Cravens took a fumble back 25 yards for a score and Josiah Taufi had a 75-yard kickoff return for the Warriors.
